Document: JointLimitationCone3D
Path: godot/classes/class_jointlimitationcone3d.rst
Summary: The angle property defines the radius range of the cone-shaped hole in joint limitations.

Property: angle (float) = 1.5707964
Setter: set_angle(value: float)
Getter: get_angle() → float
Description: The radius range of the hole made by the cone. 0 degrees creates a sphere without a hole, 180 degrees creates a hemisphere, and 360 degrees results in no limitation (empty space). The default value of 1.5707964 radians corresponds to 90 degrees.